timeline.bodyText:
I'm not sure if the functions fit into the TransactionContext - as the name implies it should contain state that is bound to the lifecycle of a transaction.
The Functions have a different lifecycle or scope. Maybe we should instead extend the evaluate method to take the Functions directly - or introduce some kind of NodeContext. Afaik we'll have other functions later that require access to the Schemas
@kovrus @seut what your take here?

